  • Rishav Goenka posted this • 8mo 8mo
    I am thrilled to share with you that I had the opportunity to work as a MarkovML Student Pioneer interacting with the best and brightest in the field. For our 'AI for Good' project we developed an intrusion detection system (IDS) using an auto encoder machine learning model.

    Our project involved training an auto encoder model using a large dataset of network traffic to detect anomalies in network behaviour. The MarkovML platform made it easy for us to preprocess and upload our dataset, as well as experiment with different auto encoder architectures to find the best one for our needs.

    One of the most helpful features of the MarkovML platform was its ability to provide real-time feedback on our model's performance. This allowed us to fine-tune our model and achieve a high level of accuracy in detecting network intrusions.

    The platform's visualisation features were also essential in helping us understand the data and model results. We were able to quickly generate visualisations of our model's predictions, allowing us to pinpoint the source of anomalies in network behaviour.

    Overall, I'm incredibly impressed with the MarkovML platform and its ability to simplify the process of building and training machine learning models. It's been an excellent experience collaborating with the team, and I'm excited to see the potential impact of our work.

    I would like to thank the entire team at MarkovML for making this such an incredible learning experience. Especially my mentors, Kushagra Arora and Sharath Savasere for guiding me through the entire program. I would also like to thank Harshwardhan Prasad and Lindsey Meyl for coming up this amazing program.

About About

I am a results-driven engineering professional with a robust educational background and a track record of impactful contributions in the fields of Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE), machine learning, and blockchain technology. My journey in these domains has seen a series of dynamic internships, where I had the opportunity to apply cutting-edge concepts to real-world scenarios.

During my tenure as a Machine Learning Pioneer Intern at MarkovML, I played a pivotal role in the development of an advanced Intrusion Detection System (IDS). Leveraging the MarkovML platform, I engineered a custom model capable of recognizing malicious patterns, thus enhancing the security of digital systems. My work extended to seamlessly integrating this model with other systems using FastAPI, ensuring efficient monitoring and reporting.

As a versatile full-stack developer at Metalok, I ventured into blockchain technology, creating smart contracts for the Polygon Chain and establishing connections between blockchain and web applications using React.js and Web3.js. This experience allowed me to manifest my passion for innovation, exemplified in the creation of Sportsverse, a blockchain-based fantasy trading platform.

My commitment to transparency and resource optimization is evident in the Supply Chain Management System I developed. This system enables clients to make secret bids, ensuring a fair distribution of resources without waste. Additionally, I delved into the world of blockchain content streaming and conceived a decentralized video streaming service using blockchain technology.

In the realm of NFTs, I introduced Raffle Time, a revolutionary concept that allows users to participate in NFT raffles, mitigating capital risks for flippers. This cross-platform application was built with Flutter, showcasing my adaptability to different programming environments.

Beyond my practical experience, my ongoing research at IIIT Hyderabad, focused on Low Earth Orbit Satellite Communications, underscores my dedication to pushing the boundaries of knowledge and technology.

Feel free to connect via LinkedIn.
